From 0e9f722d47c16cfba02d2941f2cdd17fa8815d1a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 17:55:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] Add multi-language (i18n) support for Miami launch +
 launch readiness review
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Languages: English, Spanish (es), Haitian Creole (ht), Brazilian Portuguese (pt).
Covers all four major language communities in Miami-Dade County.

Changes:
- Install i18next, react-i18next, i18next-browser-languagedetector
- src/i18n/index.ts — i18n config with browser language detection, persists
  user choice to localStorage (key: divini_lang)
- src/i18n/locales/en.ts — English source with Translations type export
- src/i18n/locales/es.ts — Spanish translation (primary Miami market)
- src/i18n/locales/ht.ts — Haitian Creole translation
- src/i18n/locales/pt.ts — Brazilian Portuguese translation
- src/components/LanguageSwitcher.tsx — compact globe-icon dropdown,
  accessible (listbox role, keyboard Escape to close)
- src/components/Shell.tsx — LanguageSwitcher in app topbar
- src/pages/Landing.tsx — LanguageSwitcher in marketing nav
- src/pages/Login.tsx — LanguageSwitcher below auth card
- src/pages/Register.tsx — LanguageSwitcher below auth card
- All 39 existing tests pass; TypeScript clean (0 errors)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_015P4doGB5hmHfHAYu31btqA
